request.description:
This sends an otp to the customer email supplied.

> _Returns (in minutes) how long an otp is valid for**If a phone number is supplied, it checks if the phone number or email already exists._

The endpoint will also check if the `email` or `phone` already exists and return an appropriate message.

Accepts:

> `email`

Optional:

> `phone`

exec: pm.test("Create/Update Customer Information data sent ", function () {

request.description:
Create or Update customer information excluding kyc documents.

Accepts:

_All parameters are nullable except otherwise stated_

> `firstname`  
> `lastname`  
> `phone`  
> `phone_default` - required if `phone` is passed, set to boolean value 1  
> `email`  
> `email_default` - required if `email` is passed, set to boolean value 1  
> `bvn`  
> `date_of_birth`: `Y-m-d`

> **Personal Data/Information**  
> _Either all or none of the parameters should be passed_  
> `gender`  
> `marital_status`  
> `maiden_name`

> **Proof of Residence/Location**  
> _Either all or none of the parameters should be passed_  
> `state_origin`  
> `lga_origin`  
> `home_address`  
> `city`  
> `state`  
> `zip_code`

> **Next of Kin Information**  
> _Either all or none of the parameters should be passed_  
> `nok_name`  
> `nok_relationship`  
> `nok_phone`  
> `nok_address`  
> `nok_city`  
> `nok_state`  
> `nok_zip_code`

> **Employer Information**  
> _Either all or none of the parameters should be passed_  
> `employer_nationality`  
> `employer_name`  
> `employer_address`  
> `employer_city`  
> `employer_state`  
> `employer_zip_code`

> **Fund Details Information**  
> _Either all or none of the parameters should be passed_  
> `fund_source`  
> `annual_income`  
> `risk_tolerance`  
> `investment_experience`  
> `investment_objective`

request.description:
This API allows for buying/selling a stock.

_NB: Account should be funded using the_ _**Funding**_ _endpoint before initiating a trade order._

Parameters:  
`cscs_number`  
`stock_code`  
`trade_action` - `buy` or `sell`  
`units`  
`order_type` - `market` or `limit`  
`date_limit(m/d/Y)` - required if `order_type` is `limit` defaults to 14 days from current date  
`request_type` - `place` or `preview`  
`price` - Current price of stock  
`price_limit` - required if `order_type` is `limit`  
`order_id` - required if `request_type` is `place`

Note: This API should be called twice with the difference been the `request_type`.  
Use `preview` for the initial call to display validity and estimated price of trade.  
Use `place` to make the actual trade.
